cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to detect semantic divergences in parallel text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural models, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of these divergences for neural machine translation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's use of neural models suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
